        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the fruit",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{sultanas}}, {{raisins}}, {{currants}}, and {{light-brown-sugar}} in a large bowl. Pour over the hot {{black-tea}}, stir, and cover. Leave overnight or for at least 8 hours. Do not drain, the remaining liquid goes into the batter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease and line a 900 g loaf tin. Beat the {{free-range-eggs}} into the soaked fruit and all its liquid. Stir in the {{self-raising-flour}} and {{mixed-spice}} until just combined. The batter will be thick and very dark.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 55 to 60 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon the batter into the prepared tin. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The top will crack slightly as it bakes. Cool in the tin for 30 minutes, then transfer to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
